                            <comment id="14560103" author="smarks" created="Tue, 14 Feb 2023 12:37:00 -0800"  >System.exit() says &amp;quot;this method never returns normally&amp;quot; which is probably a better way of expressing the sentiment intended in the Runtime.exit() spec. But it should also be made clear that neither exit() method will throw an exception if some other thread has called exit() already, or if exit() is called from a shutdown hook, or if a shutdown hook throws an exception.</comment>
